Journaling the Absurdity: Since you already rely on Notepad++ to manage your logs and thoughts, sometimes it helps to simply open a new text file and perform a "brain dump" of the encounter. Write down the Waffle House food truck idea, how it made you feel, and any other details that struck you as odd. Getting it out of your head and into a structured format can often drain the tension right out of the experience, turning a strange interaction into a funny anecdote for your friends.

Physical Grounding: Since you have a background in massage therapy and a history of endurance athletics like the Buffalo Marathon, your body likely holds onto stress in ways you are hyper-aware of. Taking a moment for some intentional stretching or breathing exercises can help release the physical tension that builds up when you are forced to engage in high-effort social situations.

